summary: For those who refuse to see Captain Marvel,
title: For those who refuse to see Captain Marvel,
body:
Ok so you don’t want to see Captain Marvel. Some say it looks bad, some think she’s unimportant, but most criticisms are about Brie herself. Here are some of my criticisms of the stuff I’m tired of hearing about Captain Marvel. 

“Why won’t she smile?” 

Do any other marvel actors smile on their posters, most likely no. You don’t really even see the main hero smile or be happy until the movie comes out. 

“Brie is a terrible actor!” 

She’s won an Oscar… come on. Don’t judge the actor based on their other non-marvel movies. Some may have a bad script, they’re doing their best. *cough cough* Star Wars prequels. 

“Brie isn’t right for Captain Marvel.” 

How do you know that? The movie isn’t out yet. She’s never even played a superhero before. Also Marvel has never miscast, ever. You will be praising her performance 43 days. 

“This is just for the SJW’s.” 

No, just no. Captain Marvel is important to the story. She’s a main character in Endgame, based on the promotional images. Yes, I think her movie should have been before Infinity War but, it is what it is. 

“It looks bad.” 

The editing process isn’t done yet. Just see the movie when it comes out, please.
